<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>VocabVault</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/styles/grammarPage.css" />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
    <link
      href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Great+Vibes&family=Knewave&family=Margarine&family=Mogra&family=Roboto+Flex:opsz,wght@8..144,100..1000&display=swap"
      rel="stylesheet"
    />
  </head>
  <body>
    <h1>Quick grammar review</h1>
    <p class="descr">Let's have a look what you've learnt!</p>
    <hr />

    <p>Beginner (A1 - A2)</p>
    <section id="A1-A2">
      <div class="dropdown">
        <button class="dropdownBtn">Nouns & Articles</button>
        <ul class="dropdownList">
          <li>
            Gender: Nouns are masculine or feminine. Masculine often ends in -o
            (e.g., niño), feminine in -a (e.g., niña).
          </li>
          <li>Definite: el (m), la (f), los (m, pl), las (f, pl).</li>
          <li>Indefinite: un (m), una (f), unos (m, pl), unas (f, pl).</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="dropdown">
        <button class="dropdownBtn">Adjectives</button>
        <ul class="dropdownList">
          <li>
            Agreement: Match gender and number of the noun (niño bueno, niña
            buena).
          </li>
          <li>Placement: Usually follow the noun (casa grande).</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="dropdown">
        <button class="dropdownBtn">Pronouns</button>
        <ul class="dropdownList">
          <li>Subject: yo, tú, él/ella, nosotros, vosotros, ellos/ellas.</li>
          <li>Object: me, te, lo/la, nos, os, los/las.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="dropdown">
        <button class="dropdownBtn">Present Tense of Verbs</button>
        <ul class="dropdownList">
          <li>
            Regular Verbs:
            <ol>
              <li>-ar: hablar → hablo, hablas, habla...</li>
              <li>-er: comer → como, comes, come...</li>
              <li>-ir: vivir → vivo, vives, vive...</li>
            </ol>
          </li>
          <li>
            Irregular Verbs:
            <ol>
              <li>Common ones include ser, estar, tener, ir.</li>
            </ol>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="dropdown">
        <button class="dropdownBtn">Basic Sentence Structure</button>
        <ul class="dropdownList">
          <li>Subject + Verb + Object: Yo como pan.</li>
          <li>Questions: Verb + Subject + Object: ¿Comes tú pan?</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="dropdown">
        <button class="dropdownBtn">Numbers</button>
        <ul class="dropdownList">
          <li>Cardinal: uno, dos, tres...</li>
          <li>Ordinal: primero, segundo, tercero...</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="dropdown">
        <button class="dropdownBtn">Time and Date</button>
        <ul class="dropdownList">
          <li>Time: Son las tres.</li>
          <li>Date: Hoy es el 3 de enero.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>
    <hr />

    <p>Intermediate (B1 - B2)</p>
    <section id="B1-B2">
      <div class="dropdown">
        <button class="dropdownBtn">Past Tenses</button>
        <ul class="dropdownList">
          <li>Preterite (completed actions): hablé, comiste, vivió.</li>
          <li>
            Imperfect (ongoing actions in the past): hablaba, comía, vivía.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="dropdown">
        <button class="dropdownBtn">Future and Conditional</button>
        <ul class="dropdownList">
          <li>
            Future: Add endings to the infinitive: hablaré, comerás, vivirá.
          </li>
          <li>
            Conditional: Add endings to the infinitive: hablaría, comería,
            viviría.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="dropdown">
        <button class="dropdownBtn">Subjunctive Mood</button>
        <ul class="dropdownList">
          <li>
            Present Subjunctive: Express wishes, doubts, or emotions. Formed by
            switching endings:
            <ol>
              <li>-ar: hable, hables, hable...</li>
              <li>-er/-ir: coma, comas, coma...</li>
            </ol>
          </li>
          <li>
            Triggered by expressions like quiero que, dudo que, es importante
            que.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="dropdown">
        <button class="dropdownBtn">Commands</button>
        <ul class="dropdownList">
          <li>Informal: Habla (positive), no hables (negative).</li>
          <li>Formal: Hable (usted), no hable.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="dropdown">
        <button class="dropdownBtn">Pronouns with Commands</button>
        <ul class="dropdownList">
          <li>Positive: Attach to verb (cómpralo).</li>
          <li>Negative: Before verb (no lo compres).</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="dropdown">
        <button class="dropdownBtn">Por vs Para</button>
        <ul class="dropdownList">
          <li>Por: Cause, duration, means (e.g., viajo por tren).</li>
          <li>
            Para: Purpose, destination, deadlines (e.g., este regalo es para
            ti).
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <hr />

    <p>Advanced (C1 - C2)</p>
    <section id="C1-C2">
      <div class="dropdown">
        <button class="dropdownBtn">Complex Subjunctive Uses</button>
        <ul class="dropdownList">
          <li>
            Past Subjunctive: Express hypothetical or past doubts/wishes.
            Hablara, comiera, viviera.
          </li>
          <li>
            If Clauses:
            <ol>
              <li>Possible: Si estudio, apruebo.</li>
              <li>Hypothetical: Si estudiara, aprobaría.</li>
            </ol>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="dropdown">
        <button class="dropdownBtn">Passive Voice</button>
        <ul class="dropdownList">
          <li>Formed with ser + past participle: El libro fue escrito.</li>
          <li>Use reflexive se for general statements: Se venden casas.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="dropdown">
        <button class="dropdownBtn">Perfect Tenses</button>
        <ul class="dropdownList">
          <li>Present Perfect: He hablado, has comido.</li>
          <li>Past Perfect: Había hablado, habías comido.</li>
          <li>Future Perfect: Habré hablado, habrás comido.</li>
          <li>Conditional Perfect: Habría hablado, habrías comido.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="dropdown">
        <button class="dropdownBtn">Advanced Sentence Structure</button>
        <ul class="dropdownList">
          <li>Relative Pronouns: que, quien, cuyo.</li>
          <li>Indirect Speech: Dijo que estudiaría mañana.</li>
          <li>
            Complex Constructions: Use of gerunds (están estudiando) and
            infinitives (después de estudiar).
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <script>
      const dropdownBtns = document.querySelectorAll(".dropdownBtn");
      const dropdownLists = document.querySelectorAll(".dropdownList");

      dropdownBtns.forEach((btn, index) => {
        btn.addEventListener("click", function () {
          const dropdownList = dropdownLists[index];
          dropdownList.style.display =
            dropdownList.style.display === "block" ? "none" : "block";
        });
      });
    </script>
  </body>
</html>
